  <TR><TD ALIGN="left" WIDTH="150">In support of its position that the step<BR ALIGN='left'/>transaction doctrine is inapplicable to<BR ALIGN='left'/>the facts of this case the Government<BR ALIGN='left'/>correctly points out that there was no<BR ALIGN='left'/>binding commitment for the merger of<BR ALIGN='left'/>Tenco to follow the acquisition of its<BR ALIGN='left'/>stock. Defendant erroneously concludes,<BR ALIGN='left'/>however, that the absence of such a<BR ALIGN='left'/>commitment here renders the step<BR ALIGN='left'/>transaction doctrine inapplicable.</TD></TR>
